{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "For the resequencing of 39 wild and cultivated C. arabica accessions, libraries were prepared using the KAPA HyperPrep Kits (Roche) following the manufacturer's instructions, and paired-end (2 × 125) sequenced on an Illumina HiSeq2500 instrument to ~40× coverage.",
    "The Linnaean herbarium sample was sequenced to 46× coverage with Ion Torrent technology.",
    "Contig-level assembly for C. canephora was obtained with MHAP 79 and scaffolded using BAC-end sequences and 454 paired-end sequences generated previously 33.",
    "Both C. eugenioides and C. arabica were assembled with Falcon 80, and C. arabica was subsequently phased using Falcon_unzip.",
    "All three genomes were error-corrected with Pilon 81 using Illumina short reads (Supplementary Section 2.2)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Contig-level assembly for C. canephora was obtained with MHAP 79 and scaffolded using BAC-end sequences and 454 paired-end sequences generated previously 33."
  ]
}